			ILLU is the short form of <b>"ILLUMINATION"</b>. You must have celebrated<b> DIWALI</b> by firing crackers, eating sweets, or maybe never celebrated it. But you could never have imagined that it can be celebrated with a feeling of <b><i>"teamwork"</i></b>! Yes, I'm not kidding you would have never seen anything like this, from weeks before the DIWALI the various halls starts making a huge structure made of 'diyas' which are lit on day of diwali. One by one these diyas are lit and slowly the "structure" starts taking its shape and delivers everyone what people were working so hard for. Even rangolis are made by various halls. I had never seen such amazing rangolis, its like they use <b><i>"technology"</i></b> in making rangolis!!! I can't express in words the essence of diwali, the level of art shown and the tempo people have for it. You will never regret that you didn't get any holidays even on diwali.
